OpenSSL Library release-signing OpenPGP public keys
===================================================

This file contains the OpenPGP certificates used to sign OpenSSL Library
source releases. Import it with either of:

    gpg --import pubkeys.asc
    sq cert import pubkeys.asc

The canonical trust anchor is the fingerprint published at
https://openssl-library.org/source/ . Keys included, in order below:

  B146 647E 45A7 B339 47AB 226B 2A2C 87D1 6169 2D40
      OpenSSL <openssl@openssl.org>
      Current release signing certificate (RSA-4096). Primary key valid
      2026-05-26 .. 2031-05-26; release artifacts are signed by its
      1-year signing subkey. This is the current trust anchor. It is also
      cross-certified by the previous release key (BA54 73A2 ... D0CB 81EF),
      so anyone who already trusts that key can confirm the transition with
      "gpg --check-sigs". That certification is carried in this file but is
      not distributed by keys.openpgp.org, which strips third-party sigs.

  BA54 73A2 B058 7B07 FB27 CF2D 2160 94DF D0CB 81EF
      OpenSSL <openssl@openssl.org>
      Previous release signing key (RSA-4096), valid until 2026-09-08.
      Used to sign earlier releases.

  EFC0 A467 D613 CB83 C7ED 6D30 D894 E2CE 8B3D 79F5
      OpenSSL OMC <openssl-omc@openssl.org>
      Older key (RSA-4096), revoked 2024-06-19. Retained so that very
      old releases can still be verified.

